						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up in a field called ‘Tenkabirti’.</p>						

						<p>Circa 14th century.</p>						

						<p>This badly damaged record refers to a gift of land by Maleyadaṇṇāyaka after purchase from the <hi rend="italic">mahājanas,</hi> and mentions Brahmāra and two persons Aṇṇa-Vōraṁbaḷi and Vishṇu-Vōraṁbaḷi. The extant portion of the record refers to a <hi rend="bold">solar eclipse.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
